            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2009-05-07 15:27:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>= mourning ritual for someone who has died, or for another tragic event; this may include {L:wailing&lt;SDBH:ילל&gt;}, tearing one's clothes, putting on {L:sackcloth&lt;SDBH:שַׂק&gt;}, covering oneself with dust or ashes, {L:fasting&lt;SDBH:צום&gt;} or eating specific food, {L:cutting oneself&lt;SDBH:גדד&gt;}, {L:shaving one's head&lt;SDBH:קרח&gt;}, covering part of one's face, etc.; this usually takes place during a specific period of time and ends after the burial has taken place, but it may also be repeated in later days to commemorate a tragic event</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>mourning</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
